The former head of the civil service in Kebbi State, Alhaji Abubakar Udu Idris on Sunday emerged as the governorship candidate of the peoples redemption party (PRP) in Kebbi state. Udu who won with 70 votes defeated his opponent Alhaji Sani Dauda Tadurga who polled 20 votes during the primaries that were held in Birnin Kebbi at Unity recreational centre, the primaries were conducted before officials of the Independent National electoral commission, party delegates and security agencies. The winner Idris thanked the delegates his words â€œI want to thank all the delegates of our great party and party stakeholders for finding me worthy of their votes, let me assure the people of Kebbi state that PRP is on a rescue mission in Kebbi state and to achieve that we need your votes and your support. -Advertisement- The former head of service was before his retirement was a seasoned administrator, technocrat and public opinion commentator and a true Nationalist who believes in the unity of Nigeria. He noted that if PRP wins the Kebbi governorship people of Kebbi should expect a massive turnaround in all the strata of government holistically.